description: Robin leads a squad undercover to investigate LexCorp.
name: True Colors

description: Black Manta sends Deathstroke and Tigress to hunt down Miss Martian.
name: The Fix

description: The four super-powered teenagers (Virgil, Sam, Tye and Ed) decide that they are sick of the testing that STAR Labs is doing. They bust out and escape, prompting Nightwing to send Blue Beetle after them. However, Red Volcano attacks the STAR Labs where Ed's father works demanding for the Amazo parts that were recently delivered there by the Justice League. Blue Beetle and the four runaways team up to take down Red Volcano. After the battle, Blue Beetle deals with the press, allowing the runaways to make their exit. As they decide their next move, Lex Luthor arrives and offers them help.
name: Runaways

description: An alien conqueror intervenes in the galactic game of supremacy.
name: War

description: Miss Martian must find a way to escape Black Manta and stop Cheshire and Sportsmaster from having their revenge on Aqualad.
name: Complications

description: The Reach are in the War World looking for the crystal key. Various squads of Reach troopers are chasing down Arsenal and other young heroes to try to prevent an intervention. Luthor sends the runaways (Virgil, Asami, Tye and Eduardo) to rescue the Team. During all of this, the Ambassador has to deal with G. Gordon Godfrey exposing the fact that the Reach has weaponized ships hidden in Earth's oceans and that they continue to hide secrets from the public.
name: The Hunt

description: The Team must find a way to rescue Blue Beetle from the Reach.
name: Intervention

description: The Light and the Reach meet to discuss the future of the entire planet.
name: Summit

description: The Team risks it all to save the Earth from the alien invasion. While the Justice League's trial on Rimbor continues, the Team and the remaining Leaguers must combine forces to end the Reach invasion on Earth.
name: Endgame

deck: 2 Doctors, what could possibly go wrong?
name: The Next Doctor

deck: Don't you just hate when the bus takes a different route?
name: Planet of the Dead

deck: What bad could a carrot do?
name: The Waters of Mars

deck: The Master returns.
name: The End of Time Part 1

deck: The return of the Time Lords!
name: The End of Time Part 2

deck: The gang run afoul of a latter-day Captain Nemo while on their way to a musical gig on Pago Pago Island.
name: The Nemo's a No-No Affair

deck: Thanks to Alexandra's scheming, the gang, thinking that they are headed to Nashville for a gig, end up in the Amazon jungle, where they encounter an evil botanist named Dr. Greenthumb, his man-eating plants, and headhunters.
name: A Greenthumb Is Not a Goldfinger

deck: While in Bombay, the gang mistakenly enters the lair of a sinister organization called the Secret Six, which plans to replace an Indian leader with one of their number with the use of a potion that can manipulate facial structure.
name: The Secret Six Secret

deck: Valerie bears an uncanny resemblance to an abducted Arabian princess and becomes involved in a plan to catch her kidnapper, a hypnotist known as the Evil Eye.
name: Swap Plot Flop

deck: While skiing in the Alps, the gang ends up in the clutches of a baron called Dr. Midas, who plans to destroy the world's entire supply of gold unless half of it is given to him.
name: Midas Mix-Up

deck: During a trip to England, the gang meets Professor Isaac Belfour, who has created an invisibility potion. Professor Belfour's former science partner, who stole the potion and used it on himself to embark on a life of crime, now calls himself Mr. X and is intent on stopping Professor Belfour from developing an antidote to the invisibility potion.
name: X Marks the Spot

deck: While in Mexico, nuclear capsules are slipped into Melody's bass drum during a fuel stop. When the henchmen for a power-mad nuclear engineer called the Scorpion snatch the drum, the gang rush to recover the instrument and become entangled in the Scorpion's scheme to rule the world with his weather control device.
name: Chili Today and Hot Tamale

deck: Melody innocently buys new shoes in Holland, unaware that they contain a message for a spy sent to stop Mastermind, a master of disguise.
name: Never Mind a Master Mind

deck: The gang's plane scheduled for Puerto Rico makes an emergency landing in a Caribbean jungle inhabited by dinosaurs and bipedal apes, all of which are under the control of a mad scientist named Dr. Madro.
name: Plateau of the Apes Plot

deck: The gang's hot air balloon is set loose and ends up on the island of Dr. Strangemoon, a mad scientist who plans to launch missiles that will devastate the Earth's atmosphere.
name: Strangemoon Over Miami

deck: Melody comes into possession of a strange ancient coin during the gang's trip to Hong Kong. The Serpent, a mad toymaker, pursues the gang in order to obtain the coin, which is key to his plans for Asian conquest.
name: All Wong in Hong Kong

deck: While on a relaxing vacation trip in Hawaii, the gang is pursued by a criminal known as the Hawk when confidential information is transferred from a tape recorder to Melody's memory.
name: Melody Memory Mix-Up

deck: While in Paris, the gang is entrusted with a mysterious black box by an agent and are told to protect it from a mysterious criminal called the Shadow. When the Shadow discovers that the gang has the black box, he and his henchmen embark on an around-the-world chase to steal it.
name: The Great Pussycat Chase

deck: The Pussycats are in New York City for a recording session. A mix-up in the mail brings them plans for a top-secret device that can deactivate the world's technology. The Pussycats' sheet music, meanwhile, ends up in the clutches of a mad criminal calling himself the Laser, who is hellbent on getting his hands on the plans that the gang now have. It is now up to the gang to hitch-hike to the Laser's hideout in the Grand Canyon and foil the fiend's plans.
name: Spy School Spoof

deck: The gang encounters an alien spaceship in Peru led by a ruthless alien named Zor, who forces the gang and the local natives to work in a diamond mine.
name: The Jumpin' Jupiter Affair

deck: The gang is invited by an eccentric countess to play a private performance on her secluded island, where they discover too late that the invitation was a ruse to obtain young test subjects for her rapid aging mist.
name: Don't Count on a Countess

description: A priest is brutally killed, and a young member of his congregation is the prime suspect. Despite the boy's affirmations of guilt, Sara suspects something else is at work. Investigating, she comes to believe that the boy was possessed by demons, and yet she still believes he was not the one responsible. She also fences with Father Del Toro, who has been assigned by the Vatican to investigate. Del Toro seems to know a great deal about the Witchblade as well, from its time when it was kept at the Vatican. Eventually Del Toro is revealed as the true murderer. Assuming demonic form, he and Sara battle and the Witchblade allows Sara to banish him.
name: Legion

deck: Aware of his new master's peculiar tastes, Krillin heads off with Goku to find Roshi a 'pretty girl.' Elsewhere, a mild mannered young lady is seen entering a bar...and exits with a completely different personality! Could this bi-polar vixen be the damsel the venerable master requires?
description: Original Title: 不思議な女の子ランチ (Fushigi na Onna no Ko Ranchi)
name: Look Out for Launch

deck: After successfully completing Roshi's first request, the two boys commence their long awaited training. After competing in a test of speed, their search and recover abilities are the next to be put to the test.
description: Original Title: 修業·石さがし (Shugyou - Ishi Sagashi)
name: Find That Stone!

description: Sara races against a ticking clock to save Conchobar when he's kidnapped and used as bait by an anti-terrorist group intent on arresting his brother for past IRA involvement. In the end, the battle for Conchobar's life becomes a battle for the Witchblade.
name: Maelstrom

description: Sara is put to the ultimate Witchblade trial. Meanwhile, Captain Dante introduces Jake to a secret brotherhood of vigilante officers who use their own methods to exact justice - will he join with them?
name: Periculum

description: Jake and Sara tail an arms dealer, but a sniper's bullet ends their chase. The case gets weirder when Sara finds a dossier among the victim's effects containing shocking details on Irons, Nottingham ...and herself!
name: Thanatopis

deck: Goku & Krillin head to bed, eagerly looking forward to tomorrow when their training commences in full. However, the breaking of dawn lands then with a rather unusual new task...They are required to deliver milk on foot, and must get it to all of their customers before Breakfast time!
description: Original Title: 命がけ!牛乳はいたつ (Inochigake! Gyuunyuu Haitatsu)
name: Milk Delivery

deck: Just when the boys thought they had it easy delivering milk daily, Goku and Krillin discover that it is but the first of many routines Master Roshi intends for them to complete daily! Soon the pint sized pair find themselves ploughing fields, doing construction work, and even swimming naked in a lake filled with sharks!
description: Original Title: 亀仙流きつーい修業 (Kamesenryuu Kitsu~i Shugyou)
name: The Turtle Hermit Way

deck: The unusual deaths of Inaba continue as the most recent victim is discovered hanging from a telephone pole. Yu, Chie, and Yosuke begin piecing things together and determine that these murders are somehow connected to the other world inside the TV. Yu and Yosuke decide to go back in, much to Chie's disapproval and once more the two boys venture into the unknown, with rope at waist but will they come back out this time?
name: The Contractor's Key

deck: Prue is attack in her Dreams.
name: Dream Sorcerer

deck: The Charmed Ones must save the groom from a demon.
name: The Wedding From Hell

deck: A teenage girl hopes to join the Halliwells.
name: The Fourth Sister

deck: Prue casts a truth spell, to find out how Andy would react to her being a witch. Which makes all the sisters tell the truth.
name: The Truth Is Out There.... and It Hurts

deck: A warlock from the past tries to steal the sisters powers.
name: The Witch Is Back

deck: Prue is framed by her boss Rex.
name: Wicca Envy

deck: Buffy must stop the Anointed One from bringing The Master back from the dead.
name: When She Was Bad

deck: With one month to go until the fabled "Budokai Tenkaichi" World Martial Arts Tournament commences, Goku & Krillin intensify their training -- and they're not alone. When they finally make it to the Tournament to sign up, Goku encounters his old friends, while also learning that Yamcha has entered the competition as well!
description: Original Title: 天下一武道会はじまる! (Tenkaichi Budoukai Hajimaru!)
name: The Tournament Begins

deck: Bulkhead absorbs a data cylinder that greatly increases his intelligence, but is also destroying him.
name: T.M.I.

deck: Ratchet 'finalizes' the synthetic energon formula and uses himself as a test subject, but it ends up having some negative side effects.
name: Stronger, Faster

deck: Spider-Man faces his first real challenge: the Enforcers and the Vulture.
name: Survival of the Fittest

deck: Peter Parker tutors Liz Allan, while Spider-Man faces Electro.
name: Interactions

deck: Dr. Curt Connors transforms into the Lizard and Peter must make a difficult decision.
name: Natrual Selection

description: Sara is investigating the murder of a pimp when she receives a mysterious package. She starts reeling when clues suggest the enemy may not be who she thought. All she can trust is herself, and hopefully... the Witchblade.
name: Apprehension

deck: One of the Big Man's Enforcers becomes Shocker.
name: Market Forces

deck: Peter and Harry, try out for the football team. Meanwhile Flint Marko becomes the Sandman.
name: Competition

deck: Peter must find a date for the Fall Formal, while Spider-Man faces a new adversary: the Rhino.
name: The Invisible Hand

deck: Peter's overconfidence is nearly his undoing, and the Tombstone is confronted by the mysterious Green Goblin.
name: Catalysts

deck: The megalomaniacal Doctor Octopus sets his sights on Norman Osborn and Spider-Man.
name: Reaction

deck: Spider-Man continues his ongoing struggle against Green Goblin, who also threatens Hammerhead and Tombstone.
name: The Uncertainty Principle

deck: During an encounter with Black Cat, Spidey gains a black costume; the Chameleon impersonates the Wall-Crawler.
name: Persona

deck: The Black-suited Spider-Man battles the Sinister Six.
name: Group Therapy

description: To Save Her Friends! Mocha Runs at the Risk of Her Life! (友達を守る! モチャ命がけの逃走, Tomodachi o Mamoru! Mocha Inochi-gake no Tōsō)
name: To Save Her Friends! Mocha Runs at the Risk of Her Life!

deck: Yukiko appears on the Midnight Channel and her best friend Chie leads the charge to rescue her. However, the police are out in force and arresting any suspicious characters, including Chie and Yukiko's best friends Yu and Yosuke.
name: We Are Friends, Aren't We?
I'll beat you, and beat you good
No One Sees the Real Me
I Want to Know the Truth
It's School Festival Day! Time to Have Fun!
We'll all meet at the AMAGIYA Hotel
In Order to Find the Truth
The World is Full of Shit
